    Product Description

    UGREEN Bluetooth Transmitter and Receiver ---- Match Your Smart Life!

    Stay Connected

    Bluetooth 5.0 provides an ultra-stable connection up to 10 m away from your device.

    The Bluetooth adapter can turn a non-Bluetooth device into a Bluetooth-enabled device as a receiver, and receive superior quality and stereo sound

    This Bluetooth Transmitter can receive and send functions integrated into one of the Bluetooth devices, long standby time, product appearance, easy to operate, free to receive and transmit audio signals.

    Extended Battery Life

    Enjoy up to 10 hours of continuous usage and charge in just 2 hours.

    Compatible with Cars

    Plug into your cars AUX port to stream music and answer calls conveniently. Just press the receiver button to answer incoming calls.

    Dual Devices

    For greater versatility, UGREEN Bluetooth receiver can simultaneously connect to two Bluetooth devices. Listen to music, answer calls, and moreat the same time

    *Certificate of authorization from the Federal Communications Commission (FCC), certificate number: [2AQI5-CM279]

    Read more

    Compact Design

    1. 3.5mm stereo audio jack

    2. microphone

    3. LED display

    4. MFB button

    5. Micro USB charging port

    Battery indicator

    Once the product has successfully paired with the phone, its performance will be displayed on the phone to better control its usage time.

    10m transmission

    With a high range of up to 10m, the signal transmission is not limited. Enjoy the absolute freedom of cables with the first-class Bluetooth technology.

    Bluetooth 5.0 & QCC Chip

    With the latest Bluetooth 5.0 & QCC chip, this UGREEN Bluetooth receiver offers enhanced sound transmission, faster pairing, more stable wireless connection and wider compatibility with Bluetooth enabled devices.

        How are ratings calculated?
        To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzes reviews to verify trustworthiness.

        2.0 out of 5 stars Does not transmit inline microphone signal from a headset!
        Reviewed in the United States on February 8, 2021
        Verified Purchase
        Contrary to what the seller or others say in the questions and answer section, this (and apparently all of these "Bluetooth receivers") do not make use of any inline microphone from attached headsets. In fact, most of these are not meant to be used for headsets, but for sticking them into a car radio 3.5mm input. It has a microphone built in so that you can use it as a car radio adapter for hands-free calls, but the quality of the mic is pretty mediocre to be honest. I'll keep searching for a device that can fully transform a wired headset *with inline-mic* into Bluetooth, but so far this has been futile... if anyone knows of such a device, please let me know in the comments!

        1.0 out of 5 stars Microphone doesn't work, makes this whole unit difficult to use.
        Reviewed in the United States on November 30, 2020
        Verified Purchase
        The microphone doesn't pick up anything you put it directly in front of your mouth and scream directly into it. Only then things are barely audible.

        And there is no way to disable the mic. When a phone call comes in your phone will automatically use the mic on this thing because it advertises itself as "hands-free" capable, so it's really annoying to have manually switch to using speakerphone every time, and this would be unsafe to do while driving.

        I would give it 4/5 stars if the mic just wasn't there to begin with, since the sound is good (it supports AAC codec so works with all Apple devices). However, I don't really need the mic, and it gets in the way and makes my phone harder to use, so giving it 1/5.

        4. Very less loss in sound quality
        5. Expecting good battery backup (mine remains connected to car's power outlet)
        6. Mic picks up the voice well during telephonic conversation (as per the feedback I received from person on the other side of the call)
        7. Comes with metalic (solid) and wired 3.5 Aux adapter, gives flexibility to one select from either two.
        8. All my previous bluetooth devices used to generate a lot of static noise while connected to the car's power outlet (may be car's wiring or earthing issue), this one I observed is not any sort of static noise. My plan was to keep it running only on its own battery that it comes with and will charge in home when the battery discharges, but as the static noise issue is not occuring anymore, I am able to keep it connected to my car's power outlet.
